title: Grateful Dead Live at Great Western LA Forum on 1989-12-09
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Adobe Audition CC2015 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Gray, Minglewood Blues, Row Jimmy, Mexicali Blues, Cumberland Blues, Bird Song, One More Saturday Night

Set 2

Foolish Heart, Playin' In The Band-> Crazy Fingers-> Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band, Drums-> Jam-> Dear Mr. Fantasy-> Hey Jude Reprise-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

reviews.review_text: My 63rd Show Similar to the previous night, good energy in the first set, though Jerry sounds tired throughout the show. Row Jimmy, not my favorite song, is really, really good here. Nice versions of Mexicali> Cumberland and Bird Song too.  And on Saturday Night, Brent has a ripping solo. Second set is a little more up-and-down. Foolish Heart is ragged. Things recover in Playin> Crazy> Uncle John’s> Playin, but still pretty mellow. Excellent Knockin encore.
